fight mode graphic enhancement guide 
SEGA/Punch-Out Style Boxing Game - Modular Outline for Copilot

Develop this game using a modular approach. Structure the code into these independent systems:

1. Rendering Module

· Fixed 640x448 resolution, 4:3, 16-bit color.
· 60 FPS pixel art. Optimize for <100 draw calls per frame.
· Optional CRT effects: light scanlines and bloom.

2. Fighter & State System

· Fighter sprites: 64x96px.
· 7-level visual damage system (fresh → critical injury).
· Separate animation modules for Movement, Offense, Defense.
· Use frame interpolation for smooth stance transitions.

3. Animation & Impact Logic

· Punch keyframe structure: Windup (2-4f), Action (2-4f), Impact (1-2f), Recovery (1-2f).
· Add 2-4 frame hit-stop on heavy punches and screen shake.

4. Interactive Ring Environment

· Persistent floor decals (scuffs, sweat, blood) that fade 20%/round.
· Elastic rope physics for sway/tension.
· 3-layer parallax background: reactive crowd, ringside NPCs, foreground corner details.

5. Effects & Particle System

· Emitters for sweat spray, blood mist, impact sparks.
· Particles with gravity, velocity, and lifetime properties.
· Dynamic overhead spotlights that dim between rounds and strobe on KOs.

6. Reactive UI/HUD

· Primary info (health/stamina bars) in top corners (Z-pattern layout).
· Include round timer, momentum bar, knockdown counter.
· Visual alerts (e.g., health bar flashes red below 20%).

Instructions for Copilot:

· Use naming: fighter{id}_{animation}_{frame}.png.
· Create separate modules/files (e.g., RenderingManager.js).
· Specify language (e.g., JavaScript/TypeScript or C#) clearly.
